HEADWORD: Ladys slipper
<hw>La"dy's slip"per</hw> <pr>(l⟦amac⟧"d⟦icr⟧z sl⟦icr⟧p"p⟦etil⟧r)</pr>
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any orchidaceous plant of the genus
<gen>Cypripedium</gen>, the labellum of which resembles a slipper. Less
commonly, in the United States, the garden balsam (<spn>Impatiens
Balsamina</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lady's smock</ent>⟦br⟧
